      "title": "Adaptive Traffic Signal Control System",
      "description": "🚦 Adaptive Traffic Control System (ATCS) – Overview\n\nAdaptive Traffic Control Systems (ATCS) are intelligent traffic management solutions that dynamically adjust signal timings based on real-time traffic conditions. Unlike traditional fixed-time signals, ATCS uses sensors, controllers, and centralized software to optimize traffic flow efficiently.\n\nKey Components:\n\nVehicle Detectors: Capture live traffic data such as volume, speed, and density\nIntersection Controllers: Execute signal timing at junctions\nCommunication Network: Connects field devices to the control center\nCentral Control System: Processes data and optimizes traffic signals\nSignal Lamps (LED): Implement traffic control actions\n\nBenefits:\n\nReduced congestion and travel delays\nImproved road capacity without infrastructure expansion\nEnhanced safety with smoother traffic flow\nLower fuel consumption and emissions\nHigh adaptability to real-time traffic scenarios\n\n👉 ATCS represents a shift from static traffic systems to data-driven, real-time optimization, playing a key role in modern smart city infrastructure.",
